<L>__{interior music center backstage area on joan night}
<A>__{equally bereaved, in front of a full length mirror, while a seamstress makes some adjustments on her gown. in the b.g., members of the chorale can be seen milling about and conversing at the close of the dress rehearsal. helen, now free of her crutches and holding a gown over her arm, moves into view, addressing her:}
<C>__{helen}
<D>__{a few of us are going to grab a bite. you want to join us?}
<C>__{joan}
<D>__{no, go ahead. i'm not hungry.}
<C>__{helen}
<D>__{well, who's going to drive you home?}
<C>__{joan}
<D>__{i will call a cab.}
<A>__{eddy steps into frame:}
<C>__{eddy}
<D>__{i can take her home.}
<C>__{helen}
<D>__{good, because i don't want you to be alone. alright?}
<P>__{(blows her a kiss)}
<D>__{see you tomorrow.}
<A>__{she moves away and joan returns her attention to the mirror, then:}
<C>__{joan}
<D>__{thank you, eddy.}
